3//###########################################################################

5// FILE: IQmathLib.h
6//
7// TITLE: IQ Math library functions definitions.
8//
9//###########################################################################
10//
11// Ver | dd-mmm-yyyy | Who | Description of changes
12// =====|=============|=======|==============================================
13// 1.3 | 19 Nov 2001 | A. T. | Original Release.
14// -----|-------------|-------|----------------------------------------------
15// 1.4 | 17 May 2002 | A. T. | Added new functions and support for
16// | | | intrinsics IQmpy, IQxmpy, IQsat.
17// -----|-------------|-------|----------------------------------------------
18// 1.4a| 12 Jun 2002 | A. T. | Fixed problem with _IQ() operation on
19// | | | variables.
20// -----|-------------|-------|----------------------------------------------
21// 1.4b| 18 Jun 2002 | A. T. | Fixed bug with _IQtoIQN() and _IQNtoIQ()
22// | | | operations.
23// -----|-------------|-------|----------------------------------------------
24// 1.4d| 30 Mar 2003 | DA/SD | 1. Added macro parameters in parentheses
25// | | | in number of places where it matters
26// | | | 2. Added macro definition to include header
27// | | | file multiple times in the program.
28// -----|-------------|-------|----------------------------------------------
29// 1.4e| 17 Jun 2004 | AT/DA | Added IQexp function.
30// | | | Added IQasin & IQacos functions (thanks DA).
31// -----|-------------|-------|----------------------------------------------
32// 1.4f| 10 Mar 2005 | AT | Fixed Bug In IQexp function.
33// -----|-------------|-------|----------------------------------------------
34// 1.5 | 30 Jan 2008 | LH | 1. Changed the definion of the _IQatan2PU(A,B)
35// | | | macro for FLOAT_MATH so that a call to
36// | | | divide will not occur.
37// | | | 2. If MATH_TYPE == FLOAT_MATH, then include the
38// | | | following standard headers: math.h
39// | | | stdlib.h.
40// | | | 3. Added missing #defines for the non-global
41// | | | _IQatanN() function
42// | | | 4. Adding missing definitions for absolute
43// | | | value when MATH_TYPE == FLOAT_MATH
44// | | | 5. Included limits.h and changed the definition
45// | | | of MAX_IQ_NEG to LONG_MIN and MAX_IQ_POS
46// | | | to LONG_MAX
47// -----|-------------|-------|----------------------------------------------
48// 1.5c| 8 June 2010 | LH | Changes made to improve porting between IQ and
49// | | | and float.
50// | | |
51// | | | 1. Added left shift and right shift #defines
52// | | | for multiplying and dividing by power of
53// | | | 2 (up to 64) for IQ_MATH
54// | | |
55// | | | 2. Added corresponding multiply/divide #defines
56// | | | for powers of 2 (up to 64) for FLOAT_MATH
57// | | |
58// | | | 3. FLOAT_MATH: Corrected the #defines for
59// | | | conversion from IQ to Q15
60// | | |
61// | | | a) removed the L on the constant to avoid
62// | | | the 64-bit float multiply call to the
63// | | | runtime support library.
64// | | | b) removed the conversion from float to
65// | | | int before the multiply. This prevented
66// | | | native floating point from being used.
67// | | |
68// | | | 4. FLOAT_MATH: Modified IQdiv and IQNdiv macros t
69// | | | such that the arguments are cast to float before
70// | | | he division.
71// | | |
72// | | | In some cases the IQ_MATH verion was used to
73// | | | divide an _iq type by an int32, which works fine.
74// | | |
75// | | | This change will allow the FLOAT_TYPE macros to
76// | | | to also be used with integer types, and not
77// | | | just "_iq" (i.e. float) types.
78// | | |
79// | | | 5. FLOAT_MATH: Changed the definition of sat for float
80// | | | math. This new definition uses compiler intrinsics and
81// | | | requires codegen tools V5.2.2 or later
82// | | | The previous definition can be uncommented
83// | | | if needed for previous versions of the codegen tools
84// | | | however it will not be efficient.
85// -----|-------------|-------|----------------------------------------------
86// 1.6.0| August 2011 | | Added LOG function
87// -----|-------------|-------|----------------------------------------------
88//###########################################################################

110//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
111// Select global Q value and scaling. The Q value is limited to the
112// following range for all functions:
113//
114// 30 <= GLOBAL_Q <= 1
115//

118#endif

225/* Fractional macro with nearest rounding (use these ONLY with literal/constant arguments!!!) */
226#define _IQRXX(x, m, q) (int32_t)((int64_t)((x >= m) ? (q - 1ULL) : ( (x <= -m) ? q : (x < 0 ? (x * q - 0.5f) : (x * q + 0.5f)) )))
227

541#define _IQtoIQ30(A) ((int32_t) (A) << (30 - GLOBAL_Q))
542#define _IQ30toIQ(A) ((int32_t) (A) >> (30 - GLOBAL_Q))
543
544#if (GLOBAL_Q >= 29)
545#define _IQtoIQ29(A) ((int32_t) (A) >> (GLOBAL_Q - 29))
546#define _IQ29toIQ(A) ((int32_t) (A) << (GLOBAL_Q - 29))
547#else
548#define _IQtoIQ29(A) ((int32_t) (A) << (29 - GLOBAL_Q))
549#define _IQ29toIQ(A) ((int32_t) (A) >> (29 - GLOBAL_Q))
550#endif
551
